      "id": "s10-29",
      "sectionId": "s10",
      "title": "useState Hook",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "javascript",
      "code": "import React, { useState } from 'react';\n\nfunction Counter() {\n  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);\n\n  return (\n    <div>\n      <p>Count: {count}</p>\n      <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>Increment</button>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\nexport default Counter;"
    },
    {
      "id": "s10-30",
      "sectionId": "s10",
      "title": "",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "Note: The useState Hook is a built-in React Hook that allows functional components to manage local state. It provides a\nway to declare state variables and update them within a functional component. Example code illustrating how to use it"
    },
